tweet_raw: Sei v2: Parallelizing the Ethereum Execution EnvironmentSei v2 is poised to become the first parallelized EVM blockchain. This major proposed update from Sei Labs aims to deploy a backward compatible Ethereum execution environment integrated into Seiâ€™s core binary inheriting Seiâ€™s advanced twin turbo consensus mechanism and optimistic parallelization capabilities while remaining fully composable with Seiâ€™s existing wasm environment.This approach means that any Ethereum or Ethereum Layer 2 application can now deploy on Sei to harness Seis speed and throughput and users can interact with Sei using familiar tools such as Metamask. The upgrade is code complete and ready for audit read more here: blog.sei.io/sei-v2-the-firstâ€¦Developers developers developers:Today Sei allows for Cosmwasm smart contracts which are written in Rust. As Sei continues to garner more developer interest the biggest request has been additional flexibility in the execution environments that Sei supports. Sei Labs has risen to this challenge with a first of its kind solution. By placing developers needs at the forefront Sei is creating the first parallelized EVM. Embracing EVM:For the first new execution environment to be integrated Sei Labs proposes to support the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) recognizing its widespread adoption. This strategic proposal acknowledges EVMs current dominance creating a familiar yet enhanced environment for the majority of blockchain developers tools and libraries.Enhancing Ethereum and Eth L2 Applications with Sei:It is often stated that â€œany large successful application on ETH requiring high throughput will pivot to being their own L2 or their own appchainâ€. Unfortunately L2s are bandwidth bound by the Ethereum base layer and fundamentally cannot scale while often simultaneously suffering from centralization trade-offs. At the same time appchains incur far more infrastructure overhead risk and complexity than many teams are willing to take on.Sei v2 will bolster any execution environment built atop it with its advanced twin turbo consensus mechanism and parallelization capabilities. This approach equips Ethereum applications to harness Seis speed efficiency and security. What does this mean?This proposed upgrade means that any EVM application can be enhanced with the benefit of 28300 batched transactions per second of throughput with 390 ms time to finality. This allows applications to support many more users and far more â€˜web-2â€™ like interactive experiences than on existing EVM blockchains. As a technology Sei offers far cheaper per-transaction costs higher throughput and the fastest time to finality in crypto while suffering from none of the centralization tradeoffs complexity or the overhead of operating an Ethereum L2 rollup.In this way Sei is making the EVM simple again.Some examples of applications that would benefit from this approach are scalable high performance dexes of any kind massive multiplayer games global payment and settlement applications and NFT projects looking to service mass global audiences. In short: applications that aspire to achieve mass adoption.Wen?Once audits are complete this upgrade will be released in a public testnet in Q1 2024 and will be deployed to mainnet in H1 2024 subject to governance.There are many other important improvements being made to Sei as part of Sei v2; you can read more here: blog.sei.io/sei-v2-the-firstâ€¦ğŸ”´âšªï¸

tweet_raw: According to JPMorgan analysts the likelihood of the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) approving an Ethereum spot exchange-traded fund (ETF) in May is uncertain with the probability of approval estimated to be no more than 50%. The regulatory ambiguity surrounding Ethereum as demonstrated by the SECs stance and recent lawsuits could potentially delay the approval process. While the crypto community eagerly anticipates an ETH spot ETF similar to Bitcoin ETFs the cautious approach from JPMorgan suggests that a positive outcome may not be guaranteed. Nonetheless if approved it is expected to have a significant impact on the price of ETH with potential growth projections until 2026. However there is also the possibility of a price pullback similar to what happened with Bitcoin after its spot ETF approval.

tweet_text: ethereums pos transition in 2024   ethereum is transitioning to proof of stake pos in 2024 replacing the current proof of work pow consensus mechanism  pos explained pos or proof of stake selects transaction validators based on the amount of eth they stake validators receive eth rewards for accurately validating transactions  advantages of pos 1 improved performance pos processes more transactions with the same resources reducing confirmation times and enhancing ethereums scalability 2 cost reduction pos consumes less energy than pow lowering transaction costs 3 enhanced security pos helps protect the network from 51 attacks where a group controls over 50 of the networks computing power to alter transaction history  impact of pos transition 1 miners wont profit from eth mining 2 users can stake eth to become validators 3 significant reduction in eth transaction fees  conclusion the shift to pos marks a significant milestone for ethereum enhancing performance reducing costs and bolstering network security
tweet_raw: **Ethereums PoS Transition in 2024 ğŸ”„ğŸš€***Ethereum is transitioning to Proof of Stake (PoS) in 2024 replacing the current Proof of Work (PoW) consensus mechanism.***PoS Explained:***PoS or Proof of Stake selects transaction validators based on the amount of ETH they stake. Validators receive ETH rewards for accurately validating transactions.***Advantages of PoS:**1. *Improved Performance:* PoS processes more transactions with the same resources reducing confirmation times and enhancing Ethereums scalability.2. *Cost Reduction:* PoS consumes less energy than PoW lowering transaction costs.3. *Enhanced Security:* PoS helps protect the network from 51% attacks where a group controls over 50% of the networks computing power to alter transaction history.**Impact of PoS Transition:**1. *Miners wont profit from ETH mining.*2. *Users can stake ETH to become validators.*3. *Significant reduction in ETH transaction fees.***Conclusion:***The shift to PoS marks a significant milestone for Ethereum enhancing performance reducing costs and bolstering network security.*

tweet_raw: COSMIC ORGASM What scientists call the Big Bang I call the cosmic orgasm. This designation seems to make more sense to me. â€œThe Big Bangâ€ sounds a bit ugly too technological not human. Cosmic orgasm - the universe explodes in orgasm. Millions of forms arise from it. And it is an experience of great bliss so we call it a cosmic orgasm. In that orgasm three things are born. First the universe what we in the East call â€˜Satâ€™. From the universe comes life what we call â€˜Anandaâ€™. And from life comes mind which we call â€˜Chitâ€™. Sat means essence ananda means praise of essence. When a plant flowers it is celebrating its being. And chit means consciousness â€“ when you are conscious of your bliss of your praise. These three states are sat chit ananda. Humanity has achieved mind. The rocks are still in the first stage the universe. They exist but they do not bloom they do not celebrate. They are closed curled up on themselves. One day they will start moving one day they will open their petals and right now they are just facing inward completely closed. Plants and animals have reached the next stage life so happy so beautiful so colorful. Birds sing endlessly and trees and plants and flowers continually bloom. This is the second stage life. The third stage can only be reached by humans: the state of mind the state of chit consciousness. Buddha said these three stages are like a dream. The first stage the stage without beginning is the original deep â€˜sleep-likeâ€™ state sushupti. These three stages are like a play unfolding. If you move beyond the mind if you start moving towards meditation towards no-mind and again another explosion happens. But now it is no longer an outward explosion it is an inward explosion. Just as the day the outward explosion occurred millions of forms were born from nothingness so when the inward explosion occurred form and identity disappeared the nothingness was born again. The circle has closed. Osho - â€œBuddhaâ€Source: Forms Are Emptiness

tweet_raw: Been busy all day #RaiderNation but I saw the #Raiders are making it official with Antonio Pierce. This is such a great story. Born in Compton grew up a Raiders Fan. Made it to the NFL as a player the hard way. He went undrafted played in Washington for a bit then joined the Giants. He worked his ass off and worked his way up to being a captain and the starting middle linebacker for the Super Bowl Champion Giants. He defeated the Patriots which is ironic because he was on Josh McDaniels coaching staff who was the offensive coordinator for the Patriots the year the Giants beat them in the Super Bowl.He found himself in a position where he was thrown in as the interim head coach when McDaniels was fired. The situation wasnt ideal but he made an impact on the players and ended with a 5-4 record and went 3-1 vs the AFC West. He won in Kansas City and led the team to a 63-21 win over the Chargers which broke the franchise scoring record. He did this by turning the defense into a top 10 unit in points allowed.  The best Raiders defense since 2002. He did it with a rookie QB and an inexperienced play caller after the HC who called the plays was fired and the OC was fired. Now he has an opportunity to do everything on his terms and he will do it the Raiders way. Hes capable of doing what he did despite the obstacles because he is a leader of men.2024 is going to be a great year for this franchise.

cs  the idea for the cs is rooted in the question how can we best ensure that holders feel valued the difficulty in solving this problem lies in the fact that people define value in many different ways some are here for vibescommunity some for the long term product vision some for the speculation so the idea of delivering value needs to somehow cut across all of this  furthermore were subject to a lot of constraints holders have been through a lot down bad markets have already assigned perceived values and holders across and within collections all have very different scales of investments and expectations  so as the cs was designed we wanted to establish a few guiding principles   double down on what makes azuki great collectibility early on the biggest differentiator azuki was always its ip and the ensuing collectibility that resulted as a private collector i like many other friends from the early days spent endless hours scanning the collection and vibing over the nuances this made living in azuki fun and we wanted to revive that   respect lore structure and history when making decisions on how the points system should work and what values should be we thought it would be tweet_raw: COLLECTOR SYSTEM 1.0In the spirit of transparency and to provide some quick thoughts/context I want to dive into CS 1.0 a bit:- Why CS?- Early post-launch reactions- Where are we goingWHY CS?The idea for the CS is rooted in the question: How can we best ensure that holders feel valued? The difficulty in solving this problem lies in the fact that people define value in many different ways; some are here for vibes/community some for the long term product vision some for the speculation. So the idea of delivering value needs to somehow cut across all of this.Furthermore weâ€™re subject to a lot of constraints; holders have been through a lot (down bad) markets have already assigned perceived values and holders *across* and *within* collections all have very different scales of investments and expectations.So as the CS was designed we wanted to establish a few guiding principles:- Double down on what makes Azuki great: COLLECTIBILITY. Early on the biggest differentiator Azuki was always its IP and the ensuing collectibility that resulted. As a private collector I (like many other friends from the early days) spent endless hours scanning the collection and vibing over the nuances. This made living in Azuki fun and we wanted to revive that.- Respect lore structure and history: When making decisions on how the points system should work and what values should be we thought it would be very important to rely on 1) foundational lore enshrined since the start (eg the focus on animals + elemental traits) 2) structure (leverage the existing trait model rather than trying to introduce new complexity on top) and 3) use historical pricing history to guide point values.Ultimately the depth of the collection meant that not literally every trait could be individually scored but we hope weâ€™ve found a good compromise.- Respect the markets. Markets are a powerful force and have already â€œweighedâ€ the value of collections. Trying to brute force new value ratios would likely end up causing a lot of disruption so we wanted to minimize that for the most part.Ultimately the goal for CS was to establish a foundation that gave us the tools and levers to make sure that we can put depth and structure around rewards. And the CS now does exactly this; instead of just being forced to think of rewards as simply one collection vs. another we now can customize rewards amongst many factors: Emblem (eg Azuki vs. Elemental Gifted vs Beastmaster) Tier (eg Grand vs. Esteemed) Level (1-5) Traits Rank (eg Order #26) and of course Score. So going forward donâ€™t expect everything to follow the same playbook. Weâ€™re going to try to mix things up every once in a while to keep things fun and interesting.

tweet_text: dogechain explains  doginals     drc20 in the name of the game frens   dogecoin builders have taken a cue from the ordinals structure on bitcoin and built their very own doginals protocol   to put it simply  drc20 or doginals are pieces of doge inscribed with rich data you can inscribe the smallest denomination of a doge shibe with additional information like artwork text music etc   the doginals protocol numbers shibes providing each shibes a unique id and tracking them through transactions   they are different from erc20 and dog20 tokens as there are no smart contracts involved in the process where nfts are minted as entirely new tokens doginals are fragments of dogecoin with data inscribed directly onto the dogecoin pow blockchain   however the absence of smart contracts also makes it challenging to plug doginals into defi and existing nft marketplaces  dogechain has always been committed to providing tooling and utility for dogecoin and addressing the wider communitys demand for different products   so the next natural step is to do the same for doginals and enhance them with defi and smart contract capability on dogechain  stay tuned for more info

These units will actively participate in shelter operations providing assistance to animals in need.Baby Doge Yards: In collaboration with shelters Baby Doge will establish new Baby Doge Community Yards where dogs and community members can play and interact. tweet_text: polkadot ecosystems top 3 revolutionary projects a deep dive into the future of decentralized tech  amidst the constellation of projects nestled within the polkadot ecosystem a select few stand out not just for their technical brilliance but for their revolutionary potential   these are the projects that push the boundaries of blockchain technology challenging the status quo and redefining whats possible in a decentralized world  1 astar network   imagine a polkadot parachain tailormade for developers a haven where smart contracts sing their sweet efficient song   enter astarnetwork   built with the substrate framework astar boasts evm compatibility allowing ethereum developers to effortlessly migrate their dapps without rewriting a single line of code   but astars magic lies deeper   its unique sharding mechanism known as horizontal state sharding promises nearinstantaneous finality and transaction fees that would make even satoshi nakamoto blush   for developers seeking a frictionless path into the polkadot world astars welcoming arms and blazingfast tracks are an irresistible combination  2 ocean protocol   data the lifeblood of the digital age is often locked away in corporate vaults inaccessible to the very individuals it concerns   oceanprotocol shatters these data silos empowering individuals to own and control their own information   its ingenious data marketplace allows users to securely buy and sell data democratizing access and unlocking a new era of datadriven innovation   underpinning this marketplace is the ingenious kilt protocol a decentralized identity solution that lets users prove their data ownership without revealing sensitive information   ocean protocols vision audacious yet attainable paints a picture of a future where data is no longer a corporate commodity but a personal asset empowering individuals and fostering a more equitable digital landscape  3 kusama   before diving headfirst into the polkadot ocean developers need a safe harbor to test their seafaring skills   kusamanetwork polkadots wild cousin provides this crucial testing ground   sharing the same codebase as polkadot kusama operates with faster release cycles and lower barriers to entry making it the perfect playground for experimentation and innovation   from audacious defi protocols to revolutionary nft marketplaces   kusamas unbridled spirit has birthed a plethora of groundbreaking projects that later find their way into the refined embrace of polkadot   think of kusama as the blockchain equivalent of silicon valleys garage startups where audacious ideas take flight fueled by the unbridled enthusiasm of a passionate community  these three projects are merely a glimpse into the vibrant tapestry woven within the polkadot ecosystem   each one in its own unique way pushes the boundaries of whats possible in the realm of decentralized technology   as polkadots network matures and its parachains flourish we can expect even more groundbreaking projects to emerge forever altering the landscape of the digital world   so fasten your seatbelts fellow explorers for the polkadot revolution has only just begun
tweet_raw: Polkadot Ecosystems Top 3 Revolutionary Projects: A Deep Dive into the Future of Decentralized Tech.Amidst the constellation of projects nestled within the #Polkadot ecosystem a select few stand out not just for their technical brilliance but for their revolutionary potential. These are the projects that push the boundaries of blockchain technology challenging the status quo and redefining whats possible in a #decentralized world.1/ Astar Network: Imagine a @Polkadot parachain tailor-made for developers a haven where smart contracts sing their sweet efficient song. Enter @AstarNetwork. Built with the Substrate framework #ASTAR boasts EVM compatibility allowing #Ethereum developers to effortlessly migrate their #DApps without rewriting a single line of code. But Astars magic lies deeper. Its unique sharding mechanism known as Horizontal State Sharding promises near-instantaneous finality and transaction fees that would make even Satoshi Nakamoto blush. For developers seeking a frictionless path into the Polkadot world Astars welcoming arms and blazing-fast tracks are an irresistible combination.2/ Ocean Protocol: Data the lifeblood of the digital age is often locked away in corporate vaults inaccessible to the very individuals it concerns. @oceanprotocol shatters these data silos empowering individuals to own and control their own information. Its ingenious data marketplace allows users to securely buy and sell data democratizing access and unlocking a new era of data-driven innovation. Underpinning this marketplace is the ingenious KILT protocol a decentralized identity solution that lets users prove their data ownership without revealing sensitive information. #Ocean Protocols vision audacious yet attainable paints a picture of a future where data is no longer a corporate commodity but a personal asset empowering individuals and fostering a more equitable digital landscape.3/ Kusama: Before diving headfirst into the Polkadot ocean developers need a safe harbor to test their seafaring skills. @kusamanetwork Polkadots wild cousin provides this crucial testing ground. Sharing the same codebase as Polkadot #Kusama operates with faster release cycles and lower barriers to entry making it the perfect playground for experimentation and innovation. From audacious #DeFi protocols to revolutionary #NFT marketplaces. Kusamas unbridled spirit has birthed a plethora of groundbreaking projects that later find their way into the refined embrace of Polkadot. Think of Kusama as the blockchain equivalent of Silicon Valleys garage startups where audacious ideas take flight fueled by the unbridled enthusiasm of a passionate community.These three projects are merely a glimpse into the vibrant tapestry woven within the Polkadot ecosystem. Each one in its own unique way pushes the boundaries of whats possible in the realm of decentralized technology. As Polkadots network matures and its #parachains flourish we can expect even more groundbreaking projects to emerge forever altering the landscape of the digital world. So fasten your seatbelts fellow explorers for the Polkadot revolution has only just begun.

tweet_raw: Polkadot 2.0 is an ecosystem to watch for this bull cycle!As you know Ive been interested into the Polkadot Ecosystem since day 1 and Ive also been invested into it. Recently Polkadot has announced the launch of Polkadot 2.0 but what is this? Whats the difference? ğŸ‘‡The changes of the Polkadot ecosystem towards Polkadot 2.0 are big as the developers behind it wanted to increase Polkadots speed safety and adaptability (which is inline with the trilemma most blockchains are confronted with).Polkadot itself has been started by one of the Ethereum co-founders Gavin Wood and he wanted to establish a cryptocurrency that delivers on the promises which Ethereum couldnt.From there Polkadot has started and surged.One of the key features with the Polkadot 2.0 ecosystem is that theyll focus on assigning its resources in an efficient way. Therefore a new system of allocating blockspace i used to make it easier to attract new projects into the Polkadot Ecosystem. As you might now Polkadot thrives from parachains and elastic cores which is a lot of technical context which you can read on the following link:wiki.polkadot.network/docs/lâ€¦Few other keypoints surrounding Polkadot 2.0:- Nominated Proof-of-Stake (NPoS): Allowing token holders to nominate validators providing more decentralisation & more stakeholders have a say in the ecosystem.- Cross-chain compatibility: Through this seamless connection between chains Polkadot parachains can connect with Ethereum and Bitcoin.- On-chain governance: This decentralized way of voting rights ensures that a more efficient decision-making process is established.I think Polkadot 2.0 will be a big deal for the ecosystem and isnt priced in. Many ecosystems havent been surging at all and Polkadot is one of them.They also got their anticipated community built meme coin $DED Airdrop coming up. Theyve got 2000+ developers within the ecosystem through which its likely that it starts to perform.On a technical perspective a small rally has occured in which I suspect that well see a retest between $5-6 as a potential case of creating a higher low.If a breakout above $9 occurs thats when things start to become great just like Chainlink has been seeing a significant breakout.

Over the weekly timeframe this altcoin has surged by 19% positioning itself as one of the top-performing altcoins in the overall market.Astar Network is paying attention to significant rebranding through Astar 2.0. With plans to promote advanced network features the protocol is poised to continually gain more acceptance potentially aiding ASTR in achieving its long-term growth ambitions.

Allowing tinkerers there to experiment again.Expect a portion of DOT from treasury to be given to KSM treasury.Expect Snowbridge to debut soon leveraging BEEFY.Potentially channeling Ethereumâ€™s vast liquidity directly into Polkadot.Enabling trustless decentralized general-purpose bridges.No reliance on human.No committees.No multisigors.Just solid code. Cryptography. Cryptoeconomics.How?BEEFY brings finality from Polkadot verifying parachain messages at low costs. Ensures that the state and txs from Polkadot are finalized and irreversible.On the Ethereum side Snowbridge includes a BEEFY light client. The Ethereum Gateway contract uses this to validate and execute Polkadotâ€™s verified finalized txs.Instead of committees and multisigors Snowbridge relies on BEEFYâ€™s randomly picked validators whose signatures get thoroughly verified. Providing a very high confidence level in the validity of cross-chain txs.Polkadotâ€™s on-chain governance free from any centralized control oversees BEEFYâ€™s updates and operations indirectly having control in how Snowbridge functions.Polkadot lending its strengths to Ethereumâ€™s challenges?Issues:Network congestion. Scaling. Inefficient and expensive blockspace allocation. Expensive DA. Fight for fee system. No bridge standardization. Smart contract risks.Current solutions:Rollup everything -> trade off decentralization initially for the sake of scaling first.ZK everything like a madman.Multisig everything for UX.Potential solutions: Shared sequencers AA enshrined rollups EIP-4844 Danksharding.Within Polkadotâ€™s design these potential solutions are already baked in its protocol not afterthoughts.Fact is fact. Ethereum has become the ultimate rollup and liquidity hub fueled by first-mover advantage adoption VC money and network effects. Yet this rollup-centric future will not allow it being a bridge hub.Todayâ€™s bridging. Bad UX. End users mostly use multisig bridges. Just in 3 years hackers filched over $2.5B.And this rollup-centric path is fraught with deep bumps and fat tail risks. It lacks standardization leads to fragmentation and leans on smart contract fidelity. Decentralization even takes a backseat as scaling takes the wheel crafting a land ruled by multisigs.Mostly for LP providers and users the stakes are high.We have Optimistic (ORU) and ZK rollups (ZKR).ORU provides more computation but longer finality period.ORU <> ZKR. Almost impossible. Thereby multisigs step in hastening finality.Canonical bridges? Whoâ€™d wait 7 days for a transfer?Shared sequencers? A maybe. Sth very similar to what Polkadot already doing with its parachains collators and relay chain.ZKR? High cost for on-chain verification.Risc0 ZETH? Brings an external service on top of Ethereumâ€™s security. Provides validity checks. Promising.But again hits the wallet hard. Demands a computer powerhouse for one proof.ORU produces a block every 2s. Bridging them with ZK. NGMI.Therefore todayâ€™s ZKR behaves more Optimistic than ZK.Polkadot steps up here. Solved and battle tested the issues of others what they canâ€™t. You can combine the Polkadot cores. Run a rollup over several cores. You have the bandwidth for heavy-duty computation. Chop and process blocks in parallel every 2s. Validate these rollup blocks akin to a ZK circuiting minus the hefty price tag.But first ETH and DOT have to talk. BEEFYâ€™s the key here making dialogue possible without a need of a translator.Hyperbridge by @PolytopeLabs integrates a complete Beacon chain light client validating Ethereumâ€™s full validator set not just a subset like other solutions do.By leveraging BEEFY using one core of Polkadot for full-scale validation. And securing this communication by Polkadotâ€™s $5B stake. Again.No multisigs.No trust assumptions.No committees in between.No subsets.#OnlyPossibleOnPolkadotAnd Polkadot gains demand by this. From the core time used for doing these processes and the computation. Win. Win.More details on this -> in the great interviews of @seunlanlege by @TEACHMEDEFI and @TheKusamarian : piped.video/jiA8sDXEbsc?si=OU0fâ€¦Data Availability?Ethereumâ€™s rollup-centric strategy hits a bandwidth wall. It canâ€™t handle all the rollup data. Expensive. So once monolithic. Today modular-wannabe.EIP4844? Just a one-hit wonder. Potential fix? Waiting on Danksharding. Wen? Vague.But now we have Celestia and Avail hosting rollup data on their chains.Polkadot though has already had Data Availability (DA) protocols for over 5 years. Each parachain block is erasure-coded and available to every relay chain validator. They can piece it back together. DAS? Re-execution of blocks? All possible.The co-founder of Polkadot @rphmeier is cooking a secret project Sugondat that aims to use Polkadotâ€™s idle cores to provide DA for other ecosystem chains. Hyperbridge collabs in here as well linking these resources to other chains/rollups.Think about it: harnessing each Polkadot core for collective computing power. Thatâ€™s how Polkadot outperforms any other DA solution thanks to its sharded execution and solid $5B security.The promise? The most efficient powerful and safe DA service for rollups and more handling storage and processing like no other can do. #OnlyPossibleOnPolkadotClosure:So can we spot the dark horse now? Or are we still enchanted by the showhorses everyone admires?Look closer see them burdened growing heavier inching closer each day to a pace it canâ€™t sustain.We do need the showhorses though for the show must go on. But when the music stops the dark horse will have to take the lead.

tweet_raw: He was a brave man from the day he was born. This is a story about Adam whose life was not easy this is the sad story of a man who fled from Janjaweed armed militias that take a central part in the atrocities of the Darfur region. He arrived in Libya in 2006 and after his father and uncles were murdered he continued from Libya to Egypt and then arrived in Israel. His path was a path full of pain loneliness and sorrow. He lived in Israel for about a decade. On October 7th he heard continuous shooting under his house in Sderot and then he heard screams he decided to go out to give aid to those who need it and try to save lives. The Hamas terrorists who captured him brutally murdered him. Adam who escaped from rape and murder was murdered by merciless terrorists in Israel which gave him refuge. His body was only identified thanks to his toothbrush after five days. His death was kept a secret for about a month the authorities wanted to get the hard news first to his mother who still lives in Darfur. tweet_text: kapparot  an annual orthodox jewish chicken ritual that happens in new york city  what is kapparot  in the week leading up to yom kippur a jewish holiday the streets of brooklyn new york become home to one of the largest wet markets in america  anywhere from 50000  100000 live chickens are used in an orthodox jewish ritual  the ritual involves orthodox jews waving a live chicken above their head reciting a prayer and then disposing of the chicken  orthodox jews believe all their sins are transferred to the chicken during this ritual and they become cleansed  what happens to the dead chickens  there are multiple ways the chickens are disposed of  1 the chicken will be slaughtered and the meat will be donated to the poor  2 the chicken will be slaughtered and the meat will be disposed off  3 in some cases the chicken will be slaughtered and left to rot  4 in more extreme cases the chicken will be beaten to death  this involves grabbing the chicken by its feet and slamming it against a hard surface repeatedly  peta have claimed that more than twothirds of the birds are simply thrown in the trash  how sanitary is it  the chickens are often kept in horrible conditions packed tightly in cages where they are left for days  in 2022 rain poured over nyc for 4 days straight and the chickens were left outdoors packed tightly in plastic crates with no food or water  many of the chickens were sick and and died in the crates yet they were still handled with bare hands by both children and the elderly  this practice is usually highly unsanitary with hygiene standards being extremely poor leaving the streets of brooklyn littered with blood feces rotting dead chickens and harmful bacteria for days  the chance of a dangerous infection spawning from the ritual is extremely high  has it been banned in nyc  there have been widespread calls to ban kapparot in nyc  some members of the jewish community also say this tradition is outdated and needs to end  to this day this orthodox jewish ritual is still practiced in new york city annually  its worth noting that kapparot takes place on a much larger scale in israel
tweet_raw: ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ğŸ” Kapparot - An Annual Orthodox Jewish Chicken Ritual That Happens in New York CityWhat is Kapparot?In the week leading up to Yom Kippur a Jewish holiday the streets of Brooklyn New York become home to one of the largest wet markets in America.Anywhere from 50000 - 100000 live chickens are used in an Orthodox Jewish ritual.The ritual involves Orthodox Jews waving a live chicken above their head reciting a prayer and then disposing of the chicken.Orthodox Jews believe all their sins are transferred to the chicken during this ritual and they become cleansed.What Happens To The Dead Chickens?There are multiple ways the chickens are disposed of:1. The chicken will be slaughtered and the meat will be donated to the poor.2. The chicken will be slaughtered and the meat will be disposed off.3. In some cases the chicken will be slaughtered and left to rot.4. In more extreme cases the chicken will be beaten to death.This involves grabbing the chicken by its feet and slamming it against a hard surface repeatedly.PETA have claimed that more than two-thirds of the birds are simply thrown in the trash.How Sanitary is It?The chickens are often kept in horrible conditions packed tightly in cages where they are left for days.In 2022 rain poured over NYC for 4 days straight and the chickens were left outdoors packed tightly in plastic crates with no food or water.Many of the chickens were sick and and died in the crates yet they were still handled with bare hands by both children and the elderly.This practice is usually highly unsanitary with hygiene standards being extremely poor leaving the streets of Brooklyn littered with blood feces rotting dead chickens and harmful bacteria for days.The chance of a dangerous infection spawning from the ritual is extremely high.Has It Been Banned in NYC?There have been widespread calls to ban Kapparot in NYC.Some members of the Jewish community also say this tradition is outdated and needs to end.To this day this Orthodox Jewish ritual is still practiced in New York City annually.Itâ€™s worth noting that Kapparot takes place on a much larger scale in Israel.
